        <mxCell id="54sLnAzViyOIR_hZKTAb-136" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;" value="Security Requirements:&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IAM Roles &amp;amp; Policies&lt;/strong&gt; (attached to Lambda/Glue/Athena/Tableau).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S3 Encryption (KMS)&lt;/strong&gt; (next to each S3 bucket).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CloudTrail Logging&lt;/strong&gt; (at the VPC boundary).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;Private VPC segmentation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="390" x="40" y="420" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <UserObject label="&lt;p style=&quot;white-space: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;  &#xa;This architecture illustrates the end-to-end data pipeline for HDB resale flat analysis. Data is ingested securely from the public &lt;span role=&quot;button&quot; tabindex=&quot;0&quot; data-url=&quot;https://data.gov.sg&quot; aria-label=&quot;data.gov.sg, this will take you to data.gov.sg&quot; style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;data.gov.sg &lt;/span&gt; API through a NAT Gateway into a private VPC, where AWS Lambda and Glue handle batch ingestion and ETL processing. Raw, cleaned, and transformed datasets are stored in Amazon S3. The transformed data is registered in the Glue Data Catalog and queried via Amazon Athena, with traffic routed privately through AWS PrivateLink to Tableau on AWS for visualization. Security is enforced through IAM roles, S3 encryption, CloudTrail logging, and strict VPC segmentation, ensuring scalability, performance, and compliance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;white-space: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" link="&lt;p style=&quot;white-space: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;  &#xa;This architecture illustrates the end-to-end data pipeline for HDB resale flat analysis. Data is ingested securely from the public &lt;span role=&quot;button&quot; tabindex=&quot;0&quot; data-url=&quot;https://data.gov.sg&quot; aria-label=&quot;data.gov.sg, this will take you to data.gov.sg&quot; style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;data.gov.sg &lt;/span&gt; API through a NAT Gateway into a private VPC, where AWS Lambda and Glue handle batch ingestion and ETL processing. Raw, cleaned, and transformed datasets are stored in Amazon S3. The transformed data is registered in the Glue Data Catalog and queried via Amazon Athena, with traffic routed privately through AWS PrivateLink to Tableau on AWS for visualization. Security is enforced through IAM roles, S3 encryption, CloudTrail logging, and strict VPC segmentation, ensuring scalability, performance, and compliance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;white-space: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" id="54sLnAzViyOIR_hZKTAb-137">
          <mxCell parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=16;" vertex="1">
            <mxGeometry height="180" width="1090" x="40" y="660" as="geometry" />
          </mxCell>
        </UserObject>
      </root>
